### Tile : get_tile()
``` lua
local tile_to_left = 	tile:get_tile( Direction.Left, 1 )
```
> The above snippet returns a **`pointer`** to the **Tile** to the left of this **Tile**.

Returns a **`pointer`** to a <%= @link_tile %> offset in one direction from this <%= @link_tile %>.

If this offset goes out of the bounds of the battlefield, or is to an otherwise invalid <%= @link_tile %>, it returns `nil` instead.

#### Function Call
`tile:get_tile( offset_direction, offset_distance )`

#### Return Value
<%= @link_tile %>

#### Parameters
<%= @link_direction %> `offset_direction`<br>
	&emsp;_The direction you want to retrieve the <%= @link_tile %> from._<br>
**`distance`** `offset_distance`<br>
	&emsp;_The number of spaces <b>(min: 0)</b> in that direction you want to retrieve the <%= @link_tile %> from._
